Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 18:55:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: resolve all critical security issues and implement real
 Pro features

CRITICAL FIXES:
1. Paywall bypass: removed is_pro property from Settings, all Pro checks
   now go through is_pro() function in usage.py which does real verification
2. Rate limiting: suggest_commit() now calls check_limit() before generating,
   free tier gets watermark appended to messages
3. Languages: added complete native system prompts for all 7 languages
   (EN, RU, ES, DE, FR, JA, ZH) instead of English-only with tag
4. Custom commit styles: implemented 5 style profiles - conventional,
   emoji, plain (free), semantic-release and gitmoji-dict (Pro only)
5. Team features: added .gitmoji-ai-team.yml support with team init/check
   commands, commit validation against team rules
6. OAuth Client ID: moved from hardcoded value to GITHUB_CLIENT_ID env var
7. Auth file security: save_github_token() now sets file permissions to 0o600
8. Action files: removed duplicate action/action.yml, consolidated to root
   action.yml with license-key input and non-destructive suggest mode
9. Device flow: implemented real GitHub Device Flow authentication with
   proper code display, polling, and PAT fallback when no client ID

PRO FEATURES IMPLEMENTED:
- Custom commit styles: semantic-release and gitmoji-dict with detailed prompts
- Team config: .gitmoji-ai-team.yml with team conventions + gmai team init/check
- All 7 languages with complete native system prompts
- Priority support: gmai support command generates debug info template

OTHER CHANGES:
- Updated README.md: removed Coming Soon, documented all real features
- Updated docs/index.html: shows real Pro features, commit styles, languages
- Added pyyaml dependency for team config YAML parsing
- Added 44 tests covering all new functionality
- Changelog now supports all 7 languages with native prompts
